    <stitle>RECONDITIONING BRAKE DRUMS AND SHOES - BRAKE DRUMS - BRAKE DRUM REPLACEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="7">
        <title>BRAKE DRUM REPLACEMENT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Proper Brake Drum Selection</title>
            <para>When specifying replacement brake drums, the following information is required:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>The manufacturer's name</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The manufacturer's part number</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Description of any other markings appearing on the drum.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>If the above information is not available, the following information is needed:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Name of manufacturer</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Model of vehicle</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Axle manufacturer and model number</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Associated wheel or hub</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Brake size and type of actuation (S-cam, Wedge, Air or Hydraulic, etc.).</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>If the information previously described is not available to properly identify the drum required, it
                will be necessary to make accurate measurements to determine the type and size of the drum needed,
                particularly if the part number cannot be determined. The following information shows and explains what
                to check and measure prior to ordering a new brake drum.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Brake drum diameter (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400714">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0400714" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400714" filename="../figg04/G0400714.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Brake Drum Diameter</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Width of brake surface (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400715" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400715" filename="../figg04/G0400715.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Width of Brake Surface</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Overall depth (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400716" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400716" filename="../figg04/G0400716.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Overall Depth</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pilot diameter (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400717" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400717" filename="../figg04/G0400717.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Pilot Diameter</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bolt circle diameter (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400718" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400718" filename="../figg04/G0400718.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Bolt Circle Diameter</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Size, number and location of bolt holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400719" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400719" filename="../figg04/G0400719.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Bolt Holes</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Are there slots in the back of the drum for wheel spoke clearance? (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0400720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0400720" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0400720" filename="../figg04/G0400720.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 20. Slots For Wheel Spoke Clearance</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>When installing new brake drums, adequate clearance must exist between the "Backwall" of
                            the brake drum and the wheel.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Mounting New Drum To Hub</title>
            <para>Drum replacement on medium and heavy duty vehicles requires the removal of nuts from bolts securing
                hub and drum together. The hub and drum can then be separated.
            </para>
            <para>Clean exposed hub or axle mounting flange with wire brush or coarse file. Use straight edge across
                surface of flange to make sure it is not bent. Remove excess paint from edge of drum hub hole and wash
                rust preventive and sealer from drum with solvent.
            </para>
            <para>Before installing a replacement drum, wash the drum thoroughly. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04007_HL0400701.xml" xrefid="hl0400701">CLEANING</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>When assembling hub and drum together, pay special attention to the bolt heads so that they are
                aligned properly in the drum.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to GROUP 02 - FRONT AXLE, or GROUP 14 - REAR AXLE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for the
                proper drum installation for the type hub used on the vehicle being serviced.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
